article.headline: Sacred Heart 24, Robert Morris 3
article.story:
FAIRFIELD, Conn. (AP) -- Freshman Jason Payne rushed for 127
yards on 28 carries to help lead Sacred Heart past Robert Morris
24-3 Saturday.

Quarterback Dan Ammel threw three touchdown passes for Sacred
Heart (6-4).

Payne rushed for 91 yards and scored a touchdown on a 31-yard
pass from Ammel.

Ammel also found Joey Henley with a 12-yard touchdown pass, and
later connected with Alvin Franklin on a 7-yard toss for a
touchdown.

Lars Anderson's 32-yard field goal gave the Pioneers a 24-3 lead
at the break. Both teams were scoreless in the second half.

Nate DiLorenzo registered the only points for Robert Morris with
a 32-yard field goal in the first quarter.

Drew Geyer completed 12 of 35 passes and 131 yards for Robert
Morris (6-5). He was intercepted twice.
